<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98676572771451></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98676572771451><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98676572771451>Unless you have Gravity Flux :></a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=13&mid=98676572771451#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Apr 8th 5:35 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At 39th enchanters get a fun and surprisingly decent AOE damage spell: Gravity Flux.<br><br>First I recommend you never cast this spell unless there is a magician or wizard in your group that has agreed to also cast AOE damage.<br><br>Second.&nbsp;&nbsp;You are gonna get pounded on, even between AOE Stuns that keep the mobs in tight formations.  Make sure you have a good healer =)<br><br>Third, this tactic takes a lot of mana is not as efficient as Mezing unless you use it on 3 or more targets at once.  However if you are camping a spawn that takes 5 to 10 minutes or more, thats enough time to earn the mana back.  Not a good tactic for constant-pull hunting.<br><br>Trust me that for those rare groups where you have 3 AOE nukers, you can drop a stack of 4 monsters before the tanks figure out who to assist next and point in the right direction..<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
